dataIdInfo.envirDesc: Microsoft Windows 7 Version 6.1 (Build 7601) Service Pack 1; Esri ArcGIS 10.1.1.3143
dataIdInfo.idPurp: Reference table for Water Quality 2010 Integrated Report Assessment.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: Table of surface water monitoring stations retrieved from Oregon DEQ's Laboratory Analytical Storage and Retrieval (LASAR) database on 11/20/2009 for evaluation and assessment for the 2010 Integrated Report. Table contains LASAR station identification, description, and latitude/longitude location information. For assessment purposes, locations were verified and other location information including latitude/longitude identifier (LLID), river mile location, and other information were added.
dataIdInfo.idCredit: Oregon DEQ Laboratory and Environmental Assessment Division, Oregon DEQ Water Quality Division

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Monitoring station identification number from LASAR.

Identification for lake, reservoir, or pond.
Water body name verified by GIS information.
The name of the coastal recreation beach used in EPA’s Beach Advisory and Closing On-Line Notification (BEACON) system for reporting pollution incidents for coastal beaches.
